      "writtenOn": "2016-08-01T22:31:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This spec:\n\nhttps://www.khronos.org/registry/egl/sdk/docs/man/html/eglChooseConfig.xhtml\n\nsays that EGL_FALSE will be returned on any error.  Your code seems to imply that config_ret might be EGL_TRUE while err is indicating some error.  Is there some reason to believe that this can happen?  That is, couldn\u0027t the if statement just ask if config_ret \u003d\u003d EGL_FALSE, and only then call s_egl.eglGetError() if so?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 188,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 188,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "a097ec02a0d162aea702a3eb7fa63dbe397a2a80",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
