      "message": "As above, the spec for eglCreateContext seems to me to imply that err !\u003d EGL_SUCCESS only if mSyncContext \u003d\u003d EGL_NO_CONTEXT, so this seems redundant.\n\n(The reason I care enough to comment is because this usage pattern makes you think the combination it implies is possible, so you ask yourself if you read the spec correctly...)",
